# InfluxDB Client
 InfluxDB is an open source time series database with no external dependencies.
 It's useful for recording metrics, events, and performing analytics.

defs.name: create_retention_policy
defs.value: fn (&self, name: &str, duration: &str, replication: &str, default: bool, db: Option<&str>) -> Result<(), error::Error>
defs.docs:
Create a retention policy for a database.
 :param duration: the duration of the new retention policy.
  Durations such as 1h, 90m, 12h, 7d, and 4w, are all supported
  and mean 1 hour, 90 minutes, 12 hours, 7 day, and 4 weeks,
  respectively. For infinite retention – meaning the data will
  never be deleted – use 'INF' for duration.
  The minimum retention period is 1 hour.
